## Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+
- npm 9+

## Setup

1. Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

2. Configure environment:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```
{{#if hasAuth}}
{{#if authRequired}}
The `{{auth.envVarName}}` value is required for authenticated endpoints.
{{else}}
The `{{auth.envVarName}}` value is optional and only needed for authenticated endpoints.
{{/if}}
{{/if}}

3. Build:

```bash
npm run build
```

4. Run:

```bash
npm start
```

## Claude Desktop Configuration

Add this to your Claude Desktop MCP config file (adjust the absolute path):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{projectName}}": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/ABSOLUTE/PATH/TO/{{projectName}}/dist/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "API_BASE_URL": "{{baseUrl}}"{{#unless (eq auth.type "none")}},
        "{{auth.envVarName}}": "replace-me"{{/unless}}
      }
    }
  }
}
```

